{"key":"processedPost-10462412","value":{"id":10462412,"first":10459904,"last":10485500,"when":1244332719,"utime":"06/07/09 02:58 AM","content":"Something to ponder: If you sealed the lid airtight, how would the air stone/pump supply any fresh air at all?&nbsp; It would just pressurize the unit until the pump melted.<br /><br />Aquarium pumps are pretty lame for fresh air.&nbsp; Mushroom mycelium benefits from fresh, moving, turbulent air, and such is also the number 1 way to prevent contaminant molds, which thrive in still, stale, non-turbulent air. You won't get much movement or turbulence from an aquarium pump feeding an airstone.&nbsp; They work better than nothing at all, but there's better ways of doing things.<br />RR","title":"Re: Rubbermaid FC - not airtight enough?"}}